article.headline: Georgia St 80, Fla Atlantic 76
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Herman Favors scored 19 of his 21 points in the second half to lead Georgia State to a 80-76 win over Florida Atlantic on Thursday night. Favors scored all of his points off the bench as Georgia State (13-12, 10-7 Atlantic Sun Conference) never trailed after the opening minute of the game. Boyd Copeland scored all 18 of his points in the first half for the Panthers while Kevin Thomas added 16 and Marcus Brown finished with 13. Florida Atlantic (9-15, 9-8) had a cold night shooting, hitting just 37.8 percent of its shots from the field. Mike Bell led the Owls with 22 points while Kahleaf Watson added 12 points and Pierre Tucker scored 10, all in the first half. Robert Williams had nine rebounds to become FAU's all-time leading rebounder. He pushed his career total to 560, moving ahead of Damon Arnette's record of 551 set in 1998-99.
